data.title: Beška, , Serbia
data.text:
Beška, Serbia is a village located in the municipality of Inđija, in the Vojvodina province. The village is situated in the southern part of the province, on the banks of the Danube River. The climate is continental, with hot summers and cold winters. Beška has a rich history, dating back to the Middle Ages. The village was first mentioned in 1411, and it was part of the Ottoman Empire from the 16th to the 19th century. Beška is home to a number of historical and cultural landmarks, including the Church of St. Nicholas, which was built in the 18th century.
